WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:07.511
Checking an entry means understanding whether the right document supports it.

2
00:00:07.511 --> 00:00:16.343
Vera starts from the sampled journal row and looks first across FatturaPA XML and authorized exports.

3
00:00:16.343 --> 00:00:23.902
It compares amount, date, document number and counterparty while keeping each source visible.

4
00:00:23.902 --> 00:00:35.703
Strong matches move into the supported set. Ambiguous cases remain in the review queue with the reason and the specific document to inspect.

5
00:00:35.703 --> 00:00:44.959
The result is a workpaper that links every checked entry to its evidence and keeps exceptions separate.

6
00:00:44.959 --> 00:00:49.200
From a sampled row to support the reviewer can follow.
